<item>
            <title>[LU-15003] use client enc_pool for fscrypt</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15003</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to Sebastien&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.eofs.eu/_media/events/lad20/lustre-client-encryption.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;fscrypt presentation at LAD&apos;20&lt;/a&gt;, the use of bounce buffers reduces fscrypt performance by up to 30%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be replaced by using preallocated pages in &lt;tt&gt;enc_pool&lt;/tt&gt; from Kerberos, so that pages do not need to be allocated/freed for every RPC.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
